3407
04:24:02,395 --> 04:24:03,676
[SPEAKER_31]: This is about human rights.

3408
04:24:03,736 --> 04:24:07,878
[SPEAKER_31]: The Office of Special Counsel found that Black Lives Matter is not a political statement.

3409
04:24:08,318 --> 04:24:19,364
[SPEAKER_31]: And to say that it is a political statement is something that you're able to do when your life, your lived experience, your day in, day out is not impacted.

3410
04:24:19,404 --> 04:24:21,645
[SPEAKER_31]: And it's a privilege to be able to say, hey, that's political.

3411
04:24:21,925 --> 04:24:24,867
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas for everyone else, for the people affected, it's a human right.

3412
04:24:25,087 --> 04:24:25,647
[SPEAKER_31]: So thank you.

3413
04:24:26,608 --> 04:24:26,888
[SPEAKER_31]: Thank you.

3414
04:24:28,188 --> 04:24:36,710
[SPEAKER_49]: And again, Mr. President, I'm going to say, if I can interject, and I appreciate Councilor Merrill for saying that, but it's easy to say what you just said.

3415
04:24:37,470 --> 04:24:40,271
[SPEAKER_49]: But the truth of the matter is, it is a political statement.

3416
04:24:40,931 --> 04:24:42,372
[SPEAKER_49]: Unfortunately, it is.

3417
04:24:42,452 --> 04:24:46,993
[SPEAKER_49]: We could all say it's not, but unfortunately it is, on both sides.

3418
04:24:48,233 --> 04:24:51,254
[SPEAKER_49]: So we need to find a way to get through this and stop hailing from that.

3419
04:24:51,514 --> 04:24:53,574
[SPEAKER_49]: We have to acknowledge this stuff and move forward.

3420
04:24:54,155 --> 04:24:54,515
[SPEAKER_49]: Thank you.

3421
04:24:54,975 --> 04:24:56,035
[SPEAKER_49]: Thank you, Councilor Scott Kelly.

3422
04:24:56,972 --> 04:25:00,753
[SPEAKER_38]: So let's see, we have Councilor Beers.

3423
04:25:02,993 --> 04:25:06,874
[SPEAKER_29]: Very quickly, this is not in any way an attempt to divide the city.

3424
04:25:06,934 --> 04:25:11,875
[SPEAKER_29]: I think what's dividing the city is decades, if not centuries of unaddressed discrimination.

3425
04:25:12,275 --> 04:25:13,415
[SPEAKER_29]: This is an attempt to heal.

3426
04:25:13,795 --> 04:25:17,796
[SPEAKER_29]: I can't say it any better than Grace about how important this is to so many people that we do this.

3427
04:25:17,876 --> 04:25:18,756
[SPEAKER_29]: So let's do it.

3428
04:25:19,016 --> 04:25:20,217
[SPEAKER_29]: This is the action we can take.

3429
04:25:20,337 --> 04:25:21,297
[SPEAKER_29]: Thank you, Mr. President.

3430
04:25:21,577 --> 04:25:22,397
[SPEAKER_37]: Thank you, Councilor Beers.

3431
04:25:25,153 --> 04:25:27,275
[SPEAKER_37]: Diane Sullivan, name and address to the record, please.

3432
04:25:33,379 --> 04:25:33,639
[SPEAKER_04]: Yes.

3433
04:25:33,759 --> 04:25:34,060
[SPEAKER_04]: Hi.

3434
04:25:34,360 --> 04:25:34,940
[SPEAKER_04]: Sorry about that.

3435
04:25:35,321 --> 04:25:36,501
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you, President Falco.

3436
04:25:37,722 --> 04:25:40,164
[SPEAKER_04]: Diane Sullivan, Jerome Street, West Medford.

3437
04:25:41,125 --> 04:25:44,947
[SPEAKER_04]: I too stand in support of hanging a banner at City Hall.

3438
04:25:44,987 --> 04:25:49,911
[SPEAKER_04]: It seems the very least that we could do to begin the necessary healing in this city.

3439
04:25:50,712 --> 04:25:52,514
[SPEAKER_04]: I appreciate what Councilor Behrs just said.

3440
04:25:52,534 --> 04:25:59,099
[SPEAKER_04]: I would argue it is certainly not making the statement Black Lives Matter that is dividing the city.

3441
04:25:59,219 --> 04:26:03,082
[SPEAKER_04]: It is the response to this necessary statement.

3442
04:26:05,404 --> 04:26:06,765
[SPEAKER_04]: There was so much more that I could say.

3443
04:26:07,005 --> 04:26:09,227
[SPEAKER_04]: My son just graduated from high school.

3444
04:26:09,267 --> 04:26:12,109
[SPEAKER_04]: He was honored with a banner along with the entire class of 2020.

3445
04:26:12,189 --> 04:26:18,294
[SPEAKER_04]: The statement Black Lives Matter is just as important to him.

3446
04:26:19,721 --> 04:26:39,686
[SPEAKER_04]: You know, Councilor Scarpelli, through you, President Falco, my own daughter had to have the conversation with her grandmother about why the statement Black Lives Matter is important and is not in fact a political statement as a young black woman dealing with racism in her life.

3447
04:26:40,566 --> 04:26:45,867
[SPEAKER_04]: And I would really encourage you all, leaders in this city,

3448
04:26:46,896 --> 04:26:49,879
[SPEAKER_04]: to really start this healing by starting with education.

3449
04:26:50,259 --> 04:26:59,387
[SPEAKER_04]: I would love to see more community forums dealing with this issue, but we have to be meaningful in this.

3450
04:26:59,847 --> 04:27:00,988
[SPEAKER_04]: So I'm going to end it there.

3451
04:27:01,069 --> 04:27:02,650
[SPEAKER_04]: I know it's been a long night for everybody.

3452
04:27:03,514 --> 04:27:04,815
[SPEAKER_04]: We need to get this banner up.

3453
04:27:04,915 --> 04:27:05,676
[SPEAKER_04]: It is a start.

3454
04:27:05,776 --> 04:27:06,896
[SPEAKER_04]: It is not divisive.

3455
04:27:07,237 --> 04:27:10,619
[SPEAKER_04]: It is miseducation, misinformation that is dividing this city.

3456
04:27:11,560 --> 04:27:19,105
[SPEAKER_04]: And so again, I just, I thank the counselors who are supporting this and all of the members in the community who have stood up in support of this.

3457
04:27:19,125 --> 04:27:19,785
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you so much.

3458
04:27:19,805 --> 04:27:26,410
[SPEAKER_37]: Thank you, Diane.

3459
04:27:27,290 --> 04:27:30,593
[SPEAKER_37]: Okay, so Matthew, you have a minute and a half.

3460
04:27:30,673 --> 04:27:32,074
[SPEAKER_37]: This is your second time.

